[m
[1mNAME[0m[m
       nologin - politely refuse a login[m
[m
[1mSYNOPSIS[0m[m
[m
       [1mnologin[0m[m
[m
[1mDESCRIPTION[0m[m
       The [1mnologin [22mcommand displays a message that an account is not available and[m
       exits non-zero. It is intended as a replacement shell field for accounts that[m
       have been disabled.[m
[m
       To disable all logins, investigate [1mnologin[22m(5).[m
[m
       If [1mSSH_ORIGINAL_COMMAND [22mis populated it will be logged.[m
[m
[1mSEE ALSO[0m[m
       [1mlogin[22m(1), [1mnologin[22m(5).[m
[m
[1mHISTORY[0m[m
       The [1mnologin [22mcommand appeared in BSD 4.4.[m
[m
